cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL

This paper deals with program semantics and properties expressed as first-order theories and sentences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the practical use of automatic generation of models for first-order theories, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper's focus on program properties and their proof could also fit under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
